Sentencas: A novel processing technique was developed to produce an in-situ nano-composite powder based on La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta{La}_{0.6}\hbox {Sr}_{0.4}\hbox {Co}_{0.2} \hbox {Fe}_{0.8}\hbox {O}_{3\text {-}{\updelta }}$$\end{document} (LSCF6428) and Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95(GDC10) for application as cathode material in intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFC).
Titulo: Effect of processing route on the properties of LSCF-based composite cathode for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The nano-composite powder was produced using glycine-nitrate solution combustion technique starting from nitrates of six metal ions.
Titulo: Effect of processing route on the properties of LSCF-based composite cathode for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The synthesized powder was characterized using X-ray diffraction (XRD), transmission electron microscopy (TEM), particle size and BET surface area analyses.
Titulo: Effect of processing route on the properties of LSCF-based composite cathode for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: XRD analysis of as-produced nano-composite powder confirmed the formation of desired phases right after combustion synthesis.
Titulo: Effect of processing route on the properties of LSCF-based composite cathode for IT-SOFC

Sentencas: The structural parameters of different phases present in the powders were estimated through Rietveld refinement of XRD data.
Titulo: Effect of processing route on the properties of LSCF-based composite cathode for IT-SOFC
